It works for me, I mean it will work with a MacOSX installation, but need pathes tweaking to work on other environments.
It needs an Arduino IDE install, but does not executes it.

don't hesitate to fork it with updated linux pathes.

I plan on rewriting a Makefile using CMake, so it will not need manual declaration of ".cpp" files for each library you need and it won't have awful sed pipes inside.